{# Evidence drill-down for a pattern card.

  Dispatched by ``card.code`` to a per-flag renderer. Most flags fall
  through to the flat chronological table (``_evidence/_flat_transactions``).
  Custom shapes — wash-deposit pairs, preloan_spike vs baseline, the
  acceleration normal-vs-spike layout, and the no-evidence explanation
  panels for recent_account_opening / payroll_absent — are dispatched
  by ``card.code`` and ship in a follow-up chunk on the same branch.

  Renders nothing when the card has no source_transactions AND no custom
  no-evidence renderer is registered for the code. That preserves the
  existing behavior for ``payroll_absent`` (empty source_ids hides the
  drill-down) until the explanation panel lands.

  Inputs:
    - card: PatternCard (from aegis.web._pattern_cards)
    - all_transactions: list[ClassifiedTransaction]  (optional; reserved
      for renderers that need full-doc context — preloan_spike baseline,
      etc. Not used by the flat fallback.)
#}
{% if card.source_transactions %}
  <details>
    <summary>{{ card.source_transactions|length }} contributing transaction row(s) — click to expand</summary>
    {# Custom dispatch lands here in a follow-up chunk. For now every
       flag falls through to the flat chronological table — the same
       shape that was previously inlined in the dossier pattern_cards
       loop, so this refactor is a no-op visually. #}
    {% include "_evidence/_flat_transactions.html.j2" %}
  </details>
{% endif %}
